sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant S as Server

    Note over C: generate connection ID
    C->>S: REQUEST (filename, connection ID, segment size)

    alt file not found
        S-->>C: ERROR
        Note over C: abort transfer
    else file found
        Note over S: split file into chunks
        S->>C: DATA (seq=0, chunk 1)
        C->>S: ACK (seq=0)

        S->>C: DATA (seq=1, chunk 2)
        C->>S: ACK (seq=1)

        Note over S,C: ... repeats for each chunk ...

        S->>C: DATA (seq=0, last chunk, payload < segment size)
        C->>S: ACK (seq=0)
        Note over C: write file to disk
    end

    alt ACK lost (server side)
        Note over S: timeout after 3s
        S->>C: DATA retransmitted (same chunk)
    end

    alt DATA lost (client side)
        Note over C: timeout after 30s
        Note over C: abort transfer
    end